```javascript
// Select the input field and table
const inputField = document.getElementById("inputField");
const tableBody = document.querySelector("tbody");
// Add an event listener to the input field
inputField.addEventListener("input", function() {
  // Filter the rows based on the input field value
  const filteredRows = tableBody.querySelectorAll("td:contains(inputField.value)");
  // Clear the filtered rows
  tableBody.innerHTML = "";
  // Append the filtered rows to the table body
  tableBody.appendChild(...filteredRows);
});
```
In this example, we first select the input field and table using their IDs. We then add an event listener to the input field that listens for changes in its value. When the value changes, we filter the tbody rows using the `querySelectorAll()` method and the `contains()` method, which selects rows that contain the input field value. We clear the tbody content and append the filtered rows to the table body using the `appendChild()` method.

